#### Awards and Honors

The accolades bestowed upon Robertson speak to the enduring impact of his work. He is a three-time recipient of the [Fulkerson Prize](/Fulkerson_Prize): in 1994 for his contributions to the Hadwiger conjecture, in 2006 for the groundbreaking Robertson–Seymour theorem, and again in 2009 for his role in proving the strong perfect graph theorem. These aren't just tokens; they are markers of significant intellectual territory conquered.

He also received the [Pólya Prize (SIAM)](/P%C3%B3lya_Prize_(SIAM)) in 2004, the OSU Distinguished Scholar Award in 1997, and the Waterloo Alumni Achievement Medal in 2002. In 2012, he was recognized as a fellow of the [American Mathematical Society](/American_Mathematical_Society), a testament to his standing within the mathematical community.

